Creating an Uber / Shadow JAR implies either Maven or Gradle is also used to handle all the library dependancies. 

If so, one solution is to run either the Maven or Gradle build command-line arg from Java (using `Runtime.exec()` command). 

A use-case for doing this programmatically is as part of a Java integration test where the Uber Jar is required (see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/77128033/testing-custom-kafka-connect-smt-using-test-containers for an example).

The following solution supports both Gradle / Maven.

## Maven

Ensure the `pom.xml` includes  the [Maven Shade Plugin](https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/) plugin e.g.

